# Godot EventSheets — enforce LF in working trees on every platform.
# The compiler emits \n and several tests are byte-exact (no-drift goldens, verify-lift,
# byte-identical round-trips); CRLF working copies from autocrlf would break them.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.gd text eol=lf
*.tres text eol=lf
*.tscn text eol=lf
*.cfg text eol=lf
*.svg text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.godot text eol=lf

# Binaries
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.ttf binary
*.zip binary
*.tres diff=eventsheet

# Semantic 3-way merge for event-sheet .tres (uid-keyed) — see docs/VERSION-CONTROL.md.
# Opt-in per clone (merge drivers live in .git/config, which isn't committed):
#   git config merge.eventsheet.driver "tools/sheet_merge.sh %O %A %B %P"
# Harmless until configured — git falls back to its default merge. Scoped to sheet folders so
# non-sheet .tres keep the default driver; add your own project's sheet folder the same way.
demo/sheets/**.tres merge=eventsheet
demo/showcase/*.tres merge=eventsheet
